# Step 10 — What happens when we include Age?

```r
colsToIgnore <- c("PassengerId", "Name", "Cabin", "Ticket")  # Age NOT ignored
input <- setdiff(names(titanic_train), c(target, colsToIgnore))
```

When `Age` is included, the model will have `NA` (missing) values in the
data. Logistic regression will **silently drop those rows** during training,
and may produce `NA` predictions during testing.

The lab shows this **on purpose** so you can see the problem, then
fixes it by putting `Age` back in `colsToIgnore`.

